Package cpsc433

The sisyphusI package is designed for the CPSC 433 Artificial Intelligence course.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    SisyphusPredicates
    This interface should be implemented by any class that reads Sisyphus I predicates.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Entity
    The base class for named things.
    Environment
    This is class extends PredicateReader just as required to in the assignment.
    ONode  
    OTree
    The or-tree, which consists of ONodes.
    Pair<K,V>
    Implements a simple key/value pair which supports the Comparable contract and the Map.Entry contract.
    Predicate
    Represents a predicate of the form predicate-name ( param , ...
    PredicateReader
    This class is responsible for interpreting arbitrary predicates.
    SearchControl
    This class serves as the search control for the search process, along with the summing of penalty points.
    SisyphusI
    This is the main class for the SysiphusI assignment.

Package cpsc433 Description

The sisyphusI package is designed for the CPSC 433 Artificial Intelligence course.
CPSC 433 Artificial Intelligence
Winter 2006
Instructor: Rob Kremer
Department of Computer Science
University of Calgary
Calgary, CANADA
The assignment is a search assignment based on the Sisyphus I project.
